        "title": "How to take heap dump in Sun JDK 1.5 (windows) programmatically",
        "body": "<blockquote>\n  <p><strong>Possible Duplicate:<\/strong><br>\n  <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/3136125/trigger-heap-dump-of-a-1-5-jvm-running-on-windows\">Trigger Heap Dump of a 1.5 JVM running on Windows<\/a>  <\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n\n\n<p>I have successfully taken heap dump in Sun JDK 1.6 (Windows) through HotSpotMXBean and by using jmap . Now , I have to do the same thing in JDK 1.5(windows).<\/p>\n\n<p>Now the problem is that , in JDK 1.5 (windows) there is no jmap  , neither does it support HotSpotMXBean. So , can you guide me how I can take heap  dump of a whole JVM in 1.5.<\/p>\n\n<p>Thanks in advance.<\/p>\n",
